Having been given some advise.Bellerophon atop a black steed,rode to Athena's temple.Bringing the beast to a halt,he smoothly dismounted then unlatching a black,ornate wooden box from the saddle.Using both arms,he carried the box to the temple entrance,then set it down.Once pushing the large temple doors open,he again gathered the box in his arms and entered the temple.Walking to the alter,he set the box down on the ground,then kneeling,he unlocks the box,and opens it.<br>
<br>
Saying silent prayers to the goddess,He began to unload the box.Pulling out a pair of golden goblets and setting them on the alter,he then took out a small pouch from the box and a silver plate,setting the silver plate on the alter,he opens the small pouch and carefully empties the contents of the bag into the silver plate,a hand full of carefully cut diamonds,rubys and other pressious gems fell into the plate.He then pulled out a long shawl of beautifully made silk with chin design and too set it on the alter.Next and the final gift in the box,he pulled out a sheathed dagger.Slightly removing the sheath,revealed a golden toned blade,with a handle of ivory,beautifully carved.He too set that upon the alter.Then closing the box up which too was a gift,he sets that upon the alter aswell.Though his gifts were few,they were the object in which Bellerophon had spent quite a bit of time and gold to get,yet he hoped they were worthy.<br>
<br>
He was going to be staying this night in the temple,for some time he kneeled near the alter saying silent prayers in his head,until the night came.He then stood,lightly brushing off his pants then moving to a corner of the temple where he sat and leaned against the wall,arms crossed over his chest,legs crossed at the ankles.<br>
<br>
He'd hope Athena would make an appearence of some sort,and help him abtain some knowledge of how to tame the wild Pegasus.<br>
<br>
)I hope ya'll know what this SL is about.It should be a little obvious,and being a bit bored at the moment,and sticking to mythos....I decided to have a go at it.( <p>-=¤ Bellerophon ¤=-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/4/01 10:43:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bellerophon's Gifts</span><hr size=1> Athena had stood there looking at Bellerophon spread his gifts about her altar. She hadn't had such things in a long while, and as much as these gifts pleased her, his silent prayers meant more.<br>
<br>
She would not make herself known to him just yet, she stood and watched until he sat back as his gifts were layed out. She smiled and in a whirl of golden fire. . .she appeared.<br>
<br>
&quot;Your pressence and gifts are welcome at my temple Bellerophon.&quot; She smiled looking down.<br>
<br>
&quot;But what brings you here?&quot;<br>
<br>
She knew what he was seeking, but she let him speak himself. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umobellerophon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MO Bellerophon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=IMG SRC="http://www.helicon.i-p.com/bellerophon-010.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/6/01 1:03:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Was he dreaming?</span><hr size=1> Bellerophon looked up at the goddess Athena as she appeared before him.He wasn't sure if this were real or if he were dreaming,but respectfully,he stood up and bowed.<br>
<br>
&quot;This is an honor.&quot;He spoke before straightening up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Great Goddess of Wisdom,I wish to tame the wild Pegasus.I have a journey to make,a beast to slay for the people of Lycia.I come to obtain the knowledge of how I can accomplish this.Will you help me?&quot; <p>-=¤ Bellerophon ¤=-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/6/01 12:50:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Pegasus</span><hr size=1> She smiled lightly at his request. She brought her hand to her chin as if to think then looked back down at him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You ask much Bellerophon. No man has ever been able to tame such a creature. Pegasus is a sacred animal. Why would I bestow you this gift?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umobellerophon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MO Bellerophon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=IMG SRC="http://www.helicon.i-p.com/bellerophon-010.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/6/01 2:34:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pegasus</span><hr size=1> &quot;The people of Lycia are of threat from the beast Chimera.I've taken up the challenge to rid the people of this threat.With Pegasus,I can accomplish this.&quot;He bowed his head slightly.<br>
<br>
&quot;With or without your help Goddess Athena,&quot; He then looked back at her. &quot;...I will face this beast.For the people of Lycia.&quot;<br>
<br>
He stood tall,his head held high.He did not fear the concept of going up against the Chimera,infact he was happy he was given the opportunity to destroy the beast.And with Pegasus,he knew he could accompish this task.<br>
<br>
 <p>-=¤ Bellerophon ¤=-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/7/01 10:54:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> To tame the wild horse</span><hr size=1> Athena smiled lightly at his answer.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bellerophon, you see yourself as a worthy warrior in the Goddess's Temple. Behold, I am that Goddess of War, she who sprang from the head of Zeus. They who prove themselves worthy in the sight of me, shall be shown great in the eyes of the Mortals. Asleep? Nay, wake. Here is what will charm the steed you covet.&quot; <br>
<br>
She vanished once more in a whirl of golden light. And Bellerophon was asleep once more. And when he woke, he would find the charm of gold resting in his palms. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umobellerophon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MO Bellerophon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=IMG SRC="http://www.helicon.i-p.com/bellerophon-010.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(8/18/01 11:55:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/alteredsoulsx/images/bellerophon-2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> He Awoke...</span><hr size=1> Bellerophon awoke the next morning and knew of what he had to do in order to tame the wild Pegasus,as he went to stand he realized the object which lay beside him.Quickly he stood and gathered the golden object in his hands,a satisfied smile upon his lips.Before leaving the temple,he looked up and quietly thanked Athena for her guidence.<br>
<br>
Leaving the temple,he goes to his horse then he slipped the golden bridle into his saddle bag,once making sure it was secure.He mounted his black steed,and kicked it into a gallop.He was on his way.<br>
<br>
